# Development Workflow

## Quick Reference

```bash
cargo build --workspace                                        # Build all crates
cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1                     # Run all tests
cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui                                   # Run the desktop app
```

> **No `source env.sh` required.** Bundled SQLite compiles with any standard C
> compiler on PATH. Lemonade Server on `localhost:13305` is auto-discovered.
> See [environment-config.mdc](mdc:.rulesdir/environment-config.mdc) for env
> vars and server setup.

---

## First Time Setup

1. Install Rust stable ([rustup.rs](https://rustup.rs)) and a C compiler
   (`gcc`, `clang`, or MSVC) — needed for `openssl-sys` (reqwest TLS).
2. *(Optional)* Install [Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade)
   for AI features. See `environment-config.mdc` for pulls.
3. `cargo build --workspace` — first build is ~30 s (bundled SQLite compilation).
4. `cargo test --workspace -- --test-threads=1` — 220+ tests pass with no
   server required.
5. `cargo run -p u-forge-ui-gpui` — launch the desktop app.

